gures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20has%20multi-generational%20institutional%20knowledge%20built%20into%20its%20Navy%20schools%2C%20training%20commands%2C%20and%20simulation%20centers.%20China%20is%20starting%20from%20scratch%20%E2%80%94%20its%20%26quot%3Bfirst%20generation%26quot%3B%20of%20carrier%20sailors%20are%20only%20now%20moving%20into%20senior%20leadership%20roles.%20Likewise%2C%20China%20is%20still%20experimenting%20with%20its%20doctrine%2C%20while%20the%20US%20Navy%20has%20had%20the%20opportunity%20for%20extensive%20iterative%20innovation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20been%20focused%20on%20training%20enlisted%20personnel%20for%20technician%20and%20operational%20carrier%20roles%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20it%20takes%20time%20because%20you%20have%20to%20build%20up%20an%20entire%20generation%20of%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Clark%20said.%20It%20can%20be%20expedited%20by%20having%20personnel%20doing%20more%20tours%20and%20increasing%20their%20experience%2C%20but%20it%20can't%20be%20skipped%20in%20the%20way%20that%20some%20technological%20and%20engineering%20hurdles%20can.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20run%20these%20carrier%20operations%2C%20especially%20in%20a%20conflict%20scenario%2C%20China%20will%20need%20to%20build%20that%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20readiness%20at%20sea%20to%20consider%20for%20a%20carrier%20fleet.%20The%20US%20has%20spent%20decades%20learning%20how%20to%20keep%20complex%20vessels%20sailing%20and%20sophisticated%20warplanes%20flying%20in%20harsh%20environments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWarships%20are%20supported%20by%20a%20global%20web%20of%20supply%20ships%2C%20repair%20hubs%2C%20and%20carefully%20managed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-navy-techs-strip-parts-fighter-jets-subs-cannibalize-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emaintenance%20cycles%3C%2Fa%3E.%20China%20may%20have%20a%20massive%20manufacturing%20workforce%20and%20can%20bring%20in%20personnel%20with%20technical%20backgrounds%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20learning%2