Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223605%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mustang%20Mach-E%20GT%20presented%20at%20the%202025%20Canadian%20International%20AutoShow.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68df16175dbc4fd10daa1741%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222401%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%26quot%3BBefore%20you%20make%20a%20big%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20CEO%20Jim%20Farley%20says%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20have%20to%20go%20and%20see%20the%20real%20problem%20%E2%80%94%20where%20the%20waste%20is.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EAnatoliy%20Cherkasov%2FInforma%20Plus%20Photo%20Agency%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFord%20is%20reinventing%20its%20manufacturing%20processes%20for%20the%20age%20of%20electric%20vehicles.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECEO%20Jim%20Farley%20credits%20a%20management%20practice%20called%20Gemba%20with%20helping%20him%20make%20better%20decisions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20process%20of%20inspecting%20production%20in%20person%20is%20a%20core%20philosophy%20of%20Ford's%20Japanese%20rival%2C%20Toyota.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%20a%20century%20after%20its%20founding%2C%20Ford%20is%20trying%20to%20reinvent%20itself%20for%20the%20age%20of%20electric%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20this%20process%2C%20CEO%20Jim%20Farley%20says%20he's%20taken%20a%20page%20from%20Japanese%20rival%20Toyota%20to%20help%20him%20make%20decisions.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20big%20decision%20I%20ever%20make%2C%20I%20go%20in%20person%2C%26quot%3B%20Farley%20told%20the%20%26quot%3BDecoder%26quot%3B%20podcast%20in%20an%20interview%20published%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hands-on%20management%20practice%20is%20called%20%26quot%3Bgemba%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20Farley%20said%20he%20%26quot%3Bfell%20in%20love%20with%20at%20Toyota%2C%26quot%3B%20where%20he%20started%20his%20automotive%20career.%20Gemba%20stems%20from%20the%20Japanese%20phrase%20%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3Bgenchi%20genbutsu%2C%26quot%3B%20meaning%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%26quot%3Bgo%20and%20see%20with%20your%20own%20eyes%2C%26quot%3B%20Farley%20said.%20The%20concept%20refers%20roughly%20to%20the%20real%20place%20where%20real%20work%20is%20done%20on%20real%20things%2C%20as%20opposed%20to%20a%20plan%20or%20model%20of%20production.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBefore%20you%20make%20a%20big%20decision%2C%26quot%3B%20Farley%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Byou%20have%20to%20go%20and%20see%20the%20real%20problem%20%E2%80%94%20where%20the%20waste%20is.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Detroit%20automaker%20is%20a%20market%20leader%20in%20producing%20cars%20and%20trucks%20with%20traditional%20internal%20combustion%20engines%20and%20powertrains%2C%20competitors%20like%20Tesla%20in%20the%20US%20and%20BYD%20in%20China%20have%20developed%20radically%20different%20approaches%20to%20manufacturing%20electric%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20rapid%20progress%20is%20pushing%20Farley%20to%20examine%20every%20aspect%20of%20production%20with%20the%20goal%20of%20wringing%20out%20as%20much%20cost%20as%20possible%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20hard%20to%20see%20from%20the%20C-suite%20where%20cuts%20can%20be%20safely%20made.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20look%20at%20it.%20You%20talk%20to%20the%20people%2C%20the%20engineers.%20'Why%20do%20we%20have%20this%20waste%3F%20Why%20do%20we%20use%20a%2025-year-old%20parts%20release%20system%3F'%26quot%3B%20Farley%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20ask%20them%20the%20basic%20questions%2C%20so%20you%20can%20visualize%20your%20decision.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Japan%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EToyota%20managers%20would%20routinely%20go%20on%20gemba%20walks%20through%20production%20facilities%20to%20observe%20how%20the%20work%20was%20being%20done%20and%20find%20ways%20to%20improve%20it%2C%20the%20company%20has%20said.%20(%26quot%3BKaizen%26quot%3B%20is%20another%20Toyota%20principle%2C%20meaning%20continuous%20improvement.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20example%20of%20something%20that%20needed%20significant%20improvement%2C%20Farley%20said%2C%20was%20a%20complex%20EV%20component%20known%20as%20a%20wiring%20loom%20for%20the%20Mustang%20Mach-E%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ean%20SUV.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20beautiful%20wiring%20loom%2C%20but%20it's%2070%20pounds%20heavier%20than%20the%20Model%20Y%20wiring%20loom%2C%20and%20it's%20%24200%20a%20battery%20to%20carry%20that%20wiring%20loom%20around%2C%20that%2070%20pounds%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ereferring%20to%20Tesla's%20competing%20Model%20Y.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFarley%20also%20found%20another%20area%20for%20improvement%20when%20comparing%20the%20two%20vehicles%20that%20most%20car%20buyers%20would%20never%20notice.%20The%20Model%20Y%20had%20a%20third%20of%20the%20fasteners%20that%20go%20into%20a%20Mach-E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20a%20manufacturability%20standpoint%20and%20a%20cost%20standpoint%2C%20you%20know%2C%20fasteners%20are%20kind%20of%20like%20it's%20an%20output%20metric%20for%20how%20elegant%20the%20simplicity%20of%20your%20engineering%20solution%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20Farley%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFarley%20said%20seeing%20the%20design%20differences%20in%20real%20life%20%E2%80%94%20and%20how%20they%20affected%20the%20production%20and%20cost%20of%20his%20cars%20%E2%80%94%20motivated%20him%20to%20make%20the%20tough%20decision%20to%20change%20some%20long-standing%20processes%20at%20the%20company%2C%20though%20it%20risked%20upsetting%20people%20who%20had%20a%20vested%20interest%20in%20those%20pieces%20of%20the%20puzzle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can't%20put%20the%20company's%20future%20at%20risk%20by%20making%20people%20happy.%20I%20have%20to%20do%20the%20right%20thing%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fford-ceo-uses-japanese-toyota-management-strategy-to-make-decisions-2025-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1759571761000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22