20the%20service%20of%20the%20right%20answer%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20a%20productive%20exercise.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESobel%20said%20the%20firm%20subscribes%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjeff-bezos-disagree-and-commit-management-philosophy-intel-andy-grove-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bdisagree%20and%20commit%26quot%3B%20mantra%3C%2Fa%3E%20popularized%20by%20Jeff%20Bezos%20at%20Amazon%2C%20as%20well%20as%20by%20former%20Intel%20CEO%20Andy%20Grove.%20When%20leaders%20at%20Trumid%20make%20a%20decision%2C%20the%20team%20gets%20on%20board%20and%2C%20regardless%20of%20how%20it%20turns%20out%2C%20%26quot%3Bthere%20is%20no%20keeping%20score%2C%26quot%3B%20Sobel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDiemand-Yauman%20and%20Taber%20Staehelin%20see%20it%20similarly.%20Early%20on%2C%20Taber%20Staehelin%20said%2C%20before%20they%20became%20%26quot%3Ba%20hive%20mind%2C%26quot%3B%20most%20disagreement%20emerged%20over%20annual%20budgeting.%20She%20said%20she%20tended%20to%20be%20more%20conservative%2C%20while%20Diemand-Yauman%20sought%20to%20be%20more%20ambitious%20in%20his%20approach%20to%20investing%20in%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20resolve%20disputes%2C%20Taber%20Staehelin%20said%2C%20the%20pair%20would%20step%20back%20to%20refocus%20on%20what%20they%20were%20trying%20to%20accomplish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20really%20tested%20the%20rigor%20of%20the%20thinking%20in%20a%20way%20that%20was%20exponentially%20beneficial%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Rebecca%20Taber%20Staehelin%20holds%20a%20rose%20that%20Connor%20Diemand-Yauman%20gave%20her%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e01de55dbc4fd10daa2c07%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERebecca%20Taber%20Staehelin%20still%20has%20the%20rose%20that%20Connor%20Diemand-Yauman%20gave%20her%20when%20they%20decided%2