ation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20I%20did%20it%2C%20and%20the%20patient%20herself%20was%20typing%20in%20and%20giving%20additional%20information%20to%20the%20chatbot%2C%26quot%3B%20Rodman%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20three-way%20conversation%20with%20the%20two%20of%20us%20in%20ChatGPT.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERodman%20is%20one%20of%20over%20a%20dozen%20healthcare%20professionals%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ewho%20spoke%20to%20Business%20Insider%20about%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20daunting%20task%20of%20choosing%20which%2C%20if%20any%2C%20AI%20tools%20to%20use.%20Many%20use%20general-purpose%20models%20like%20ChatGPT%2C%20but%20those%20may%20not%20be%20specialized%20enough%20%E2%80%94%20or%20could%20hallucinate%20faulty%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20choose%20to%20bring%20in%20a%20medical%20technology%20startup.%20In%20the%20first%20half%20of%202025%2C%20AI-enabled%20medical%20startups%20raised%2062%25%20of%20digital%20health%20venture%20funding%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Frockhealth.com%2Finsights%2Fh1-2025-market-overview-proof-in-the-pudding%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERock%20Health%3C%2Fa%3E's%20data.%20The%20period%20also%20saw%20%246.4%20billion%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ein%20venture%20funding%20poured%20into%20digital%20health%20companies%2C%20compared%20to%20%246%20billion%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20generative%20AI%20is%20still%20young%2C%20many%20of%20these%20tools%20have%20yet%20to%20face%20significant%20field%20testing%2C%20leading%20many%20hospitals%20to%20extensively%20trial%20and%20pilot%20these%20tools%20in-house.%20These%20tests%20look%20for%20medical%20ethics%20%E2%80%94%20and%20whether%20the%20tools%20are%20helpful%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20healthcare%20professionals%20still%20choose%20not%20to%20touch%20the%20tech%20at%20all.%20According%20to%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.elsevier.com%2Fabout%2Fpress-releases%2Felseviers-clinician-of-the-future-2025-survey-clinicians-ai-usage-and%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElsevier%20Health%3C%2Fa%3E%20survey%2C%2048%25%20of%20doctors%20reported%20using%20an%20AI%20tool%20in%20their%20work.%20That%20number%20is%20rapidly%20growing%2C%20though%2C%20having%20stood%20at%2026%25%20the%20year%20prior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr.%20David%20Zhang%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68bb4105f9db348adc0af69f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESomos%20Community%20Care%20pathologist%20David%20Zhang.%3Cp%3ECorrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDoctors%20we%20spoke%20to%20had%20some%20common%20ground%2C%20with%20almost%20all%20using%20an%20AI%20device%20to%20automate%20one%20of%20the%20most%20repetitive%20parts%20of%20their%20job%3A%20taking%20notes.%20Beyond%20that%2C%20they%20varied%20widely%20in%20where%20they%20thought%20AI%20was%20helpful%20%E2%80%94%20and%20safe.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20doctors%20are%20using%20ChatGPT%20%E2%80%94%20and%20not%20just%20for%20email-writing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AI%20giants%20are%20positioning%20themselves%20in%20the%20medical%20market.%20At%20a%20recent%20Federal%20Reserve%20conference%2C%20OpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20said%20that%20ChatGPT%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bbetter%20diagnostician%20than%20most%20doctors%20in%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%20Google%20and%20Microsoft%20have%20specialized%20medical%20models%3B%20Microsoft's%20model%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Ftechnology%2F2025%2Fjun%2F30%2Fmicrosoft-ai-system-better-doctors-diagnosing-health-conditions-research%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E4x%20more%20accurate%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20human%20diagnosticians%20in%20solving%20case%20studies%2C%20its%20AI%20CEO%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20doctors%20who%20spoke%20with%20Business%20Insider%20used%20a%20general-purpose%20chatbot%20in%20their%20practice.%20Some%20used%20enterprise-level%20models%20that%20couldn't%20train%20on%20the%20data%2C%20and%20others%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Esaid%20they%20avoided%20feeding%20any%20sensitive%20information%20to%20the%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Brownstein%20said%20Boston%20Children's%20Hospital%2C%20where%20he%20is%20chief%20innovation%20officer%2C%20launched%20a%20HIPAA-compliant%20ChatGPT%20that%20guards%20protected%20health%20information.%20Almost%2030%25%20of%20employees%20now%20use%20it.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EHe%20listed%20some%20examples%3A%20generating%20letters%20of%20reference%2C%20quantitative%20data%20analysis%2C%20or%20combing%20through%20internal%20documents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrownstein%20also%20works%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealthcare-startups-using-ai-see-more-patients-chase-profits-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAI%20startups%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20his%20bar%20for%20these%20tools%20keeps%20rising.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20era%20of%20AI%20coding%20tools%2C%20what%20once%20took%20a%20whole%20team%20of%20engineers%20can%20increasingly%20be%20done%20with%20only%20a%20handful%20%E2%80%94%20so%20Brownstein%20said%20the%20hospital%20can%20make%20their%20own%20version%20in-house.%20Some%20medical%20technology%20startups%20are%20also%20trying%20to%20use%20AI%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bhook%2C%26quot%3B%20Brownstein%20said%2C%20making%20it%20difficult%20to%20separate%20the%20truly%20helpful%20from%20the%20bandwagon%20riders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20how%20many%20of%20these%20AI%20startups%20are%20pitching%20him%3F%20%26quot%3BIt's%20like%20dozens%20every%20week%2C%26quot%3B%20Brownstein%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20relentless.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20our%20call%2C%20Somos%20Community%20Care%20pathologist%20David%20Zhang%20demonstrated%20ChatGPT's%20response%20to%20a%20prostate%20biopsy.%20The%20chatbot%20said%20that%20an%20image%20of%20the%20biopsy%20was%20consistent%20with%20ductal%20adenocarcinoma%2C%20a%20form%20of%20pancreatic%20cancer.%20That%20diagnosis%20was%20%26quot%3Bfar%20from%20accurate%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20why%20we%20have%20a%20secure%20job%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhang%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe%20can%20make%20the%20foundation%20model%20do%20better.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228541%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr%20David%20Zhang%20at%20the%20computer%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68bb3df1f9db348adc0af5f2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225694%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EZhang%20fed%20ChatGPT%20a%20prostate%20biopsy.%20The%20chatbot's%20diagnosis%20was%20%26quot%3Bfar%20from%20accurate.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ECorrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20doctors%20looking%20for%20more%20than%20the%20average%20ChatGPT%20response%2C%20they%20may%20seek%20out%20more%20specialized%20technology.%20There%20are%20hundreds%2C%20if%20not%20thousands%2C%20for%20them%20to%20choose%20from.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fda.gov%2Fmedical-devices%2Fsoftware-medical-device-samd%2Fartificial-intelligence-enabled-medical-devices%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFDA's%20list%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20AI-enabled%20medical%20devices%20currently%20has%201%2C247%20entries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAI%20was%20supposed%20to%20come%20in%20and%20help%20streamline%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20dentist%20Divian%20Patel.%20%26quot%3BWhat%20it%20became%20is%20a%20thousand%20portals%2C%20a%20thousand%20logins%2C%20and%20nobody%20wants%20to%20use%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatel%20is%20betting%20that%20his%20fellow%20dentists%20are%20willing%20to%20pay%20to%20simplify.%20He%20and%20Shervin%20Molayem%2C%20another%20dentist%2C%20cofounded%20Trust%20AI.%20The%20company%20ostensibly%20combines%20many%20of%20these%20AI%20services%20on%20one%20platform%2C%20and%20has%20raised%20%246%20million%20in%20seed%20funding%2C%20per%20PitchBook.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERebecca%20Mishuris%2C%20the%20chief%20medical%20information%20officer%20for%20Mass%20General%20Brigham%2C%20said%20that%20she%20tries%20not%20to%20have%20%26quot%3Bshiny%20object%20syndrome%26quot%3B%20when%20judging%20the%20generative%20AI%20tools%20that%20come%20across%20her%20desk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20offering%20solutions%20for%20problems%20I%20just%20don't%20have%2C%26quot%3B%20Mishuris%20said.%20%26quot%3BMaybe%20I'll%20have%20it%20a%20year%20from%20now%2C%20but%20I%20just%20don't%20have%20it%20today.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%228687%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr.%20David%20Zhang's%20hand%20on%20the%20computer%20mouse%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68bb428cf9db348adc0af6ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225791%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EZhang%20said%20that%20doctors%20had%20a%20%26quot%3Bsecure%20job%26quot%3B%20because%20they%20can%20make%20foundation%20models%20do%20better.%3Cp%3ECorrie%20Aune%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAlan%20Weiss%2C%20an%20SVP%20of%20clinical%20advancement%20for%20hospital%20system%20Banner%20Health%2C%20said%20that%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Balmost%20overwhelming%26quot%3B%20how%20many%20of%20his%20vendors%20were%20pitching%20new%20AI%20tools.%20He's%20careful%20with%20which%20new%20tech%20he%20takes%20on%2C%20having%20two%20independent%20groups%20review%20tools%20for%20both%20ethical%20and%20clinical%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELike%20many%20other%20industries%2C%20hospitals%20are%20also%20trying%20to%20use%20AI%20for%20administrative%20work.%20Doctors%20who%20spoke%20with%20Business%20Insider%20reported%20using%20AI%20for%20patient%20check-ins%20and%20to%20process%20health%20insurance%20claims.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20tools%20don't%20always%20live%20up%20to%20their%20hype.%20Last%20year%2C%20Rodman%20said%20that%20the%20industry%20was%20buzzing%20about%20AI-written%20messages%20to%20patients.%20Then%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjamanetwork.com%2Fjournals%2Fjamanetworkopen%2Ffullarticle%2F2817615%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudies%20came%20out%3C%2Fa%3E%20demonstrating%20that%20some%20doctors%20spent%20more%20time%20correcting%20the%20messages%20than%20hand-writing%20them%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20have%20all%20pretty%20much%20fizzled%20out%2C%26quot%3B%20Rodman%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20an%20area%20where%20there%20was%20a%20lot%20of%20excitement%20that%20hasn't%20lived%20up%20to%20the%20promise.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20doctors%20Business%20Insider%20interviewed%20ranged%20from%20excited%20AI%20practitioners%20to%20skeptics.%20But%20most%20of%20the%20doctors%20agreed%20on%20the%20power%20of%20one%20tool%3A%20ambient%20listening%20devices.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20AI-powered%20note-taking%20devices%20listen%20in%20on%20conversations%20between%20doctors%20and%20patients%2C%20summarizing%20insights%20in%20one%20document.%20Mishuris%20said%20the%20devices%20have%20%26quot%3Breal%20transformative%20power.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225687%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr.%20Carl%20Dirk%20in%20his%20praxis.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68bb420832af4d666ef761b0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223791%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECarl%20Dirks%20said%20ambient%20listening%20limited%20the%20%26quot%3Bcognitive%20drain%26quot%3B%20of%20note-taking.%3Cp%3EChase%20Castor%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECarl%20Dirks%2C%20an%20internal%20medicine%20physician%20at%20St.%20Luke's%20in%20Kansas%20City%2C%20called%20ambient%20listening%20a%20solution%20to%20%26quot%3Bclinician%20burnout.%26quot%3B%20Some%20primary%20care%20physicians%20told%20him%20that%20the%20tool%20extended%20their%20careers%20by%20limiting%20the%20%26quot%3Bcognitive%20drain%26quot%3B%20of%20fast%20note-taking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20really%20trying%20to%20restore%20human-to-human%20connection%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Philip%20Payne%2C%20Dirk's%20colleague%20and%20chief%20health%20AI%20officer%20at%20BJC%20Healthcare.%20%26quot%3BHow%20do%20we%20get%20the%20computer%20out%20of%20the%20way%20so%20that%20the%20provider%20and%20the%20patient%20have%20a%20conversation%20rather%20than%20the%20provider%20sitting%20behind%20a%20keyboard%20and%20typing%20the%20whole%20time%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20official%20rule%20or%20guideline%20about%20how%20to%20disclose%20the%20use%20of%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finside-messiest-relationship-in-healthcare-ai-abridge-epic-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eambient%20listening%20device%3C%2Fa%3E.%20However%2C%20doctors%20have%20a%20legal%20obligation%20to%20disclose%20the%20device's%20use%20in%20states%20with%20two-party%20recording%20laws.%20Some%20hospitals%20also%20set%20disclosure%20policies%20for%20all%20their%20providers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatients%20then%20need%20to%20decide%20if%20they're%20comfortable%20with%20their%20chats%20being%20recorded%20and%20processed%20by%20AI.%20The%20quality%20of%20the%20disclosure%20matters%20here%3A%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Farticles%2FPMC12284739%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJuly%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20121%20ambient%20documentation%20pilots%2C%20nearly%2075%25%20of%20patients%20surveyed%20were%20comfortable%20with%20the%20technology's%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20psychiatrist%2C%20Farhan%20Hussain's%20notes%20are%20fairly%20extensive.%20He%20loved%20using%20an%20ambient%20listening%20device%20in%20previous%20jobs%2C%20but%20no%20longer%20has%20access%20in%20his%20new%20role%20at%20a%20telehealth%20firm.%20He%20misses%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOtherwise%2C%20we%20really%20are%20taking%20notes%20the%20whole%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Hussain%20said.%20%26quot%3BLike%20damn%2C%20I%20didn't%20go%20to%20med%20school%20to%20just%20become%20a%20scribe.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmbient%20listening%20is%20also%20teeming%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvcs-clamoring-invest-medical-scribe-ai-startups-abridge-ambience-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eventure%20funding%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%20July%2C%20Ambience%20Healthcare%20raised%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fbusinessinsider.com%2Fambience-healthcare-used-this-pitch-deck-to-raise-243-million-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%24243%20million%20in%20Series%20C%3C%2Fa%3E%20funding%20backed%20by%20Oak%20HC%2FFT%20and%20Andreessen%20Horowitz.%20Nabla%20raised%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.prnewswire.com%2Fnews-releases%2Fnabla-raises-70m-series-c-to-deliver-agentic-ai-to-the-heart-of-clinical-workflows-bringing-total-funding-to-120m-302483646.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2470%20million%20Series%20C%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20June%2C%20led%20by%20HV%20Capital.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%226000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dr.%20Carls%20Dirk%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68bb418c32af4d666ef76195%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDirks'%20colleague%20Philip%20Payne%20said%20that%20ambient%20listening%20helps%20%26quot%3Brestore%20human-to-human%20connection.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EChase%20Castor%20for%20BI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20number%20of%20well-funded%20ambient%20companies%20leaves%20doctors%20with%20additional%20choices.%20Brownstein%20uses%20Abridge%2C%20Hussain%20uses%20Nabla%2C%20and%20Weiss%20is%20currently%20piloting%20four%20different%20ambient%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrancisco%20Lopez-Jimenez%20believes%20cardiology%20is%20one%20of%20the%20most%20technology-forward%20medical%20disciplines%2C%20likely%20because%20of%20his%20peers'%20backgrounds%20in%20physics%20and%20computer%20science.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCardiology%20has%20really%20been%20at%20the%20front%20of%20innovation%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lopez-Jimenez%2C%20Mayo%20Clinic's%20codirector%20of%20AI%20in%20cardiology.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20one%20of%20the%20fields%20that%20started%20using%20and%20developing%20AI%20the%20earliest%20in%20medicine%2C%20no%20question.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELopez-Jimenez%20is%20quick%20to%20admit%20bias%20%E2%80%94%20he%20is%20a%20cardiologist%20himself%2C%20after%20all.%20Pierre%20Elias%2C%20medical%20director%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20at%20New%20York-Presbyterian%20Hospital%20and%20yet%20another%20cardiologist%2C%20agreed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20FDA%20clearance%20for%20AI%20technology%2C%20it's%20radiology%20and%20cardiology%20that%20have%20led%20the%20path%2C%26quot%3B%20Elias%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20radiologists%20don't%20interface%20with%20patients%20quite%20as%20much%20as%20cardiologists%20do.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20wide%20swaths%20of%20medicine%2C%20a%20gulf%20is%20emerging%20between%20the%20eager%20and%20the%20skeptical.%20According%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fassets.ctfassets.net%2Fo78em1y1w4i4%2FT7F5sDDiUC8KJzLQXfJoy%2F004be7f43562d318115a294cf626be7f%2FClinicianOfTheFuture_2025.pdf%3Futm_source%3Dbanner%26utm_medium%3Ddg%26utm_campaign%3Dcotf%26utm_content%3Drpt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EElsevier%20Health%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2048%25%20of%20clinicians%20surveyed%20said%20they%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Euse%20AI%20in%20their%20practice%20%E2%80%94%20but%2024%25%20still%20don't%20use%20the%20technology%20at%20all%2C%20even%20in%20non-work%20settings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20gulf%2C%20then%2C%20are%20the%20doctors%20rejecting%20AI%20on%20its%20face.%20Maybe%20they're%20worried%20about%20ethics%20or%20about%20losing%20their%20tact.%20Indeed%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flangas%2Farticle%2FPIIS2468-1253(25)00133-5%2Fabstract%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAugust%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20asked%20doctors%20who%20regularly%20use%20AI%20to%20perform%20a%20colonoscopy%20without%20its%20assistance.%20Before%20their%20AI%20use%2C%20adenoma%20detection%20was%20at%2028.4%25%3B%20after%2C%20it%20declined%20to%2022.4%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJonathan%20Simon%2C%20an%20internal%20medicine%20physician%20at%20Bayhealth%2C%20said%20there%20was%20only%20%26quot%3Bone%20area%26quot%3B%20where%20he%20used%20AI%3A%20note-taking.%20He%20does%20not%20touch%20a%20general%20model%20like%20ChatGPT%20or%20any%20of%20the%20emerging%20med%20tech%20players%20in%20his%20practice%2C%20though%20he's%20attended%20some%20AI%20research%20talks%20that%20have%20intrigued%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimon%20worried%20about%20efficiency%20gains.%20He%20recognized%20that%20faster%20diagnoses%20mean%20a%20quicker%20rate%20of%20seeing%20patients%20%E2%80%94%20something%20that%20could%20be%20lucrative%20for%20doctors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20that%20desire%20to%20throughput%20as%20many%20patients%20as%20possible%2C%20because%20that's%20where%20the%20money%20is%2C%20the%20industry%20really%20has%20to%20keep%20an%20eye%20on%20responsible%20and%20consistent%20use%20of%20AI%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMistakes%20might%20be%20rare%2C%20but%20a%20rare%20mistake%20can%20destroy%20someone's%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-doctors-use-ai-chatgpt-including-to-help-avoid-burnout-2025-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1759570561000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e024d65dbc4fd10daa2d80%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-doctors-use-ai-chatgpt-including-to-help-avoid-burnout-2025-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Over%20a%20dozen%20healthcare%20professionals%20told%20Business%20Insider%20how%20they%20use%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20including%20one%20way%20it%20could%20h